text: Seema Malhotra (born 7 August 1972) is a British Labour and Co-operative Party politician. She has been the Member of Parliament (MP) for Feltham and Heston since a by-election was held following the death of Alan Keen in 2011. ==References== Category:1972 births Category:Living people Category:Labour Party (UK) MPs
title: Seema Malhotra
